<Layout title="About — decod.ing">
  <article class="prose container">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span><h1>Developer utilities without the trust tax.</h1><p
      class="lead"
    >
      decod.ing is a free, zero-account universal decoder and 47-tool local workbench.
    </p><p>
      It is built around one rule: developer payloads are data to inspect on your device, not
      content to upload to somebody else's service.
    </p><h2>Business model</h2><p>
      All features remain free. If the site reaches its quality and traffic gates, a single
      self-hosted contextual sponsor may appear below the tool. Desktop, CLI, PWA standalone,
      workspace, and browser extension surfaces remain ad-free.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
